Sign in to the Azure portal: Go to the Azure portal and sign in with your Azure account.

Navigate to Azure Active Directory: In the left-hand navigation pane, click on "Azure Active Directory".

Register an application:

Click on "App registrations" under "Manage".
Click on "New registration".
Enter a name for your application.
Select the appropriate Supported account types (e.g., Accounts in this organizational directory only).
Enter a Redirect URI (optional).
Click on "Register".
Retrieve the Client ID:

Once your application is registered, you'll be taken to the overview page.
Copy the "Application (client) ID". This is your Client ID.
Generate a Client Secret:

In the left-hand menu, click on "Certificates & secrets" under "Manage".
Click on "New client secret".
Enter a description, select an expiry period, and click on "Add".
Copy the generated value immediately. This is your Client Secret.
Save the Client Secret:

Store the Client Secret securely, as you won't be able to retrieve it later.
